The '''Biak scrubfowl''' or '''Biak megapode''' ('''''Megapodius geelvinkianus''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Megapodiidae]]. It is found only on the islands of [[Biak]], [[Mios Korwar]], [[Numfor]], [[Manim]] and [[Mios Num]] in the [[West Papua (region)|West Papua]] region of [[Indonesia]].

== Description ==
This bird measures {{convert|36|cm|in|abbr=on}} long. Its plumage is largely dark grey. It has a slight crest and a reddish or bluish face. Legs are red or dark grey.<ref name=BirdLife/>

== Habitat ==
Its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]] and [[subtropical or tropical moist shrubland]]. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

Some taxonomists consider this to be a subspecies of the [[dusky megapode]], others as a subspecies of the [[orange-footed scrubfowl]], but is increasingly looked at as a distinct species.

